verses.text:
"Now when Jesus was come into the parts of Caesarea Philippi, he asked his disciples, saying, Who do men say that I the Son of man am?" - Matt. 16:13.
One sweetly solemn thought Comes to me o'er and o'er; I am nearer to my home to-day, Than I've been be-fore;
Nearer my Father's house, Where many mansions be; Nearer the throne where Jesus sits, Nearer the crys-tal sea.
